6","of, Calverley, Yorkshire, England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1136–":"about 1136–Deceased","1136–Male":"1136–Deceased","1176–Male":"1176–Deceased","1111–Male":"1111–Deceased","1113–Female":"1113–Deceased","1136":"1136","1113":"1113","1111":"1111","1176":"1176","Abt 1136":"about 1136","of, Calverley, Yorkshire, England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Calverley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): habitational name from Calverley in Yorkshire, named with Old English <i>calfra</i> (genitive plural of <i>calf</i> ‘calf’) + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Alternatively, in some instances the name may be a variant of the habitational name <b>Calveley</b>, from a place so called in Cheshire (with the same meaning as above), or from Calverleigh in Devon, meaning ‘the clearing of the bare wood’ (Old English <i>calu</i> ‘bare, bald’ + <i>wudu</i> ‘wood’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Calvery","meanings":["English: shortened form of   Calverley  .","Possibly an Americanized form of German <b>Kälberer</b>(see   Kalberer  )."]},{"name":"Caverly","meanings":["English (Middlesex): shortened form of   Calverley  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Scot","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Although this was in use as a personal name both before and after the Norman Conquest, modern use in most cases almost certainly represents a transferred use of the surname. This originated as a byname for someone from Scotland or, within Scotland itself, for a member of the Gaelic-speaking people who originally came from Ireland. The given name is now often chosen by parents conscious of their Scottish ancestry and heritage, but it is also used more widely."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Scot de Calverley Ld of Calverley was born about 1136, in Calverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Le Scot Steward of Empress Maud, was 27 and his mother, Larderina de Calverley, was 25. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1136–":"umbes 1136–Surnud","1136–Male":"1136–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1111–Male":"1111–Surnud","1113–Female":"1113–Surnud","1136":"1136","1113":"1113","1111":"1111","1176":"1176","Abt 1136":"umbes 1136","of, Calverley, Yorkshire, England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1136–":"noin 1136–Kuollut","1136–Male":"1136–Kuollut","1176–Male":"1176–Kuollut","1111–Male":"1111–Kuollut","1113–Female":"1113–Kuollut","1136":"1136","1113":"1113","1111":"1111","1176":"1176","Abt 1136":"noin 1136","of, Calverley, Yorkshire, England":"Calverley, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1136–":"environ 1136–Décédé","1136–Male":"1136–Décédé","1176–Male":"1176–Décédé","1111–Male":"1111–Décédé","1113–Female":"1113–Décédée","1136":"1136","1113":"1113","1111":"1111","1176":"1176","Abt 1136":"environ 1136","of, Calverley, Yorkshire, England":"Calverley, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John Scot de Calverley Ld of Calverley est né environ 1136, à Calverley, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, John Le Scot Steward of Empress Maud, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Larderina de Calverley, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1136–":"um 1136–Verstorben","1136–Male":"1136–Verstorben","1176–Male":"1176–Verstorben","1111–Male":"1111–Verstorben","1113–Female":"1113–Verstorben","1136":"1136","1113":"1113","1111":"1111","1176":"1176","Abt 1136":"um 1136","of, Calverley, Yorkshire,